#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.79"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.79:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.79:0.2"
msgid "8. Ānandavagga "
msgstr "8. Ānanda "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.79:0.3"
msgid "79. Gandhajātasutta "
msgstr "79. Fragrances "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.79:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.79:2.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhante, gandhajātāni, yesaṃ anuvātaṃyeva gandho gacchati, no paṭivātaṃ. "
msgstr "“Sir, there are these three kinds of fragrance that spread only with the wind, not against it. "

msgctxt "an3.79:2.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.79:2.3"
msgid "Mūlagandho, sāragandho, pupphagandho—"
msgstr "The fragrance of roots, heartwood, and flowers. "

msgctxt "an3.79:2.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhante, tīṇi gandhajātāni, yesaṃ anuvātaṃyeva gandho gacchati, no paṭivātaṃ. "
msgstr "These are the three kinds of fragrance that spread only with the wind, not against it. "

msgctxt "an3.79:2.5"
msgid "Atthi nu kho, bhante, kiñci gandhajātaṃ yassa anuvātampi gandho gacchati, paṭivātampi gandho gacchati, anuvātapaṭivātampi gandho gacchatī”ti? "
msgstr "Is there a kind of fragrance that spreads with the wind, and against it, and both ways?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.226, sc3
#. VAR: Atthānanda, kiñci gandhajātaṃ → atthānanda gandhajātaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.79:3.1"
msgid "“Atthānanda, kiñci gandhajātaṃ yassa anuvātampi gandho gacchati, paṭivātampi gandho gacchati, anuvātapaṭivātampi gandho gacchatī”ti. "
msgstr "“There is, Ānanda, such a kind of fragrance.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.79:3.2"
msgid "“Katamañca pana, bhante, gandhajātaṃ yassa anuvātampi gandho gacchati, paṭivātampi gandho gacchati, anuvātapaṭivātampi gandho gacchatī”ti? "
msgstr "“So what, sir, is that kind of fragrance?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.79:4.1"
msgid "“Idhānanda, yasmiṃ gāme vā nigame vā itthī vā puriso vā buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, saṅghaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, "
msgstr "“It’s when, Ānanda, in some village or town, a woman or man has gone for refuge to the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "an3.79:4.2"
msgid "pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti, sīlavā hoti kalyāṇadhammo, "
msgstr "They don’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or take alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. They’re ethical, of good character. "

msgctxt "an3.79:4.3"
msgid "vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgo payatapāṇi vossaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato. "
msgstr "They live at home with a heart rid of the stain of stinginess, freely generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to give and to share. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.79:5.1"
msgid "Tassa disāsu samaṇabrāhmaṇā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti: "
msgstr "Ascetics and brahmins everywhere praise them for these good qualities; "

#. VAR: amukasmiṃ → asukasmiṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.79:5.2"
msgid "‘amukasmiṃ nāma gāme vā nigame vā itthī vā puriso vā buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, saṃghaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.79:5.3"
msgid "pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti, musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti, sīlavā hoti kalyāṇadhammo, "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.79:5.4"
msgid "vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgo payatapāṇi vossaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc6
#. VAR: Devatāpissa → devatāpissa amanussā (bj, pts1) | devatāpissa amanussāpi (mr) | devatāpissa …pe… manussāpissa (?)
msgctxt "an3.79:6.1"
msgid "devatāpissa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti: "
msgstr "even the deities praise them. "

msgctxt "an3.79:6.2"
msgid "‘amukasmiṃ nāma gāme vā nigame vā itthī vā puriso vā buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, saṃghaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti, "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.79:6.3"
msgid "pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti … pe … surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti, sīlavā hoti kalyāṇadhammo, "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.79:6.4"
msgid "vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati muttacāgo payatapāṇi vossaggarato yācayogo dānasaṃvibhāgarato’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.79:6.5"
msgid "Idaṃ kho taṃ, ānanda, gandhajātaṃ yassa anuvātampi gandho gacchati, paṭivātampi gandho gacchati, anuvātapaṭivātampi gandho gacchatīti. "
msgstr "This is the kind of fragrance that spreads with the wind, and against it, and both. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an3.79:7.1"
msgid "Na pupphagandho paṭivātameti, "
msgstr "The fragrance of flowers doesn’t spread against the wind, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: tagaramallikā → taggaramallikā (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.79:7.2"
msgid "Na candanaṃ tagaramallikā vā; "
msgstr "nor sandalwood, pinwheel flowers, or jasmine; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.79:7.3"
msgid "Satañca gandho paṭivātameti, "
msgstr "but the fragrance of the good spreads against the wind; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.79:7.4"
msgid "Sabbā disā sappuriso pavāyatī”ti. "
msgstr "a good person’s virtue spreads in every direction.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.79:7.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

